<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1676,1702]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Remarks:</emphasis>
The original collector’s label (
<figureCitation box="[625,736,1676,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,787,811]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,186,761]" captionTargetId="figure-24@16.[149,1437,181,763]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Labels of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection described by T. Salvadori. a) Ptilotis erythropleura NHMO-BI-86778 (collector’s label); b) Melanocharis chloroptera NHMO-BI-61863 (NHMO label); c) Zosterops novae guineae NHMO-BI-86649 (NHMO label); d) Dicaeum misoriense NHMO-BI-61856 (collector’s label)." pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Figure 6a</figureCitation>
) is still attached, showing that this is specimen 
<emphasis box="[1289,1303,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">g</emphasis>
of the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1677,1703]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">type</typeStatus>
series (
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[230,406,1711,1737]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori 1881</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<emphasis box="[475,515,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">‘p.’</emphasis>
in the locality name is an abbreviation for 
<emphasis box="[996,1070,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">‘piedi’</emphasis>
, i.e. feet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<bibRefCitation author="Arbocco, G. &amp; Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C." box="[199,438,1745,1771]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="184 - 265" refId="ref13577" refString="Arbocco, G., Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C. (1979) Catalogo dei tipi di uccelli del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 82, 184 - 265." type="journal article" year="1979">
Arbocco 
<emphasis box="[302,358,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
(1979)
</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<specimenCount box="[512,672,1745,1772]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">three syntypes</specimenCount>
in Genoa (C.E. 11455–11457), and according to Enrico Borgo at the MSNG (pers. comm.) these are specimens 
<emphasis box="[630,644,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">b</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[657,671,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">h</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[725,733,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">i</emphasis>
, respectively, as listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[1026,1218,1780,1806]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
. The latter of these, specimen 
<emphasis box="[263,271,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">i</emphasis>
, is not one of the 
<typeStatus box="[469,571,1815,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">syntypes</typeStatus>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[582,770,1815,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
stated that specimens 
<emphasis box="[1020,1062,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">a–h</emphasis>
are the types, which is also in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[314,515,1849,1876]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="896 - 976" refId="ref16237" refString="Salvadori, T. (1876 a) Descrizione di cinquantotto nuove specie di uccelli, ed osservazioni intorno ad altre poco note, della Nuova Guinea e di altre Isole Papuane, raccolte dal D. r Odoardo Beccari e dai cacciatori del Sig. A. A. Bruijn. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 7, 896 - 976. [1875]" type="journal article" year="1876">Salvadori (1876a)</bibRefCitation>
basing his description on eight individuals only. Another 
<typeStatus box="[1153,1240,1850,1876]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">syntype</typeStatus>
(MZUT Av4127) is in MRSN 
<quantity box="[288,326,1885,1911]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" unit="in" value="3.0">
<superScript attach="left" box="[288,296,1885,1899]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">3</superScript>
in
</quantity>
Turin (
<bibRefCitation author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[411,640,1885,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis box="[513,571,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
); this corresponds to specimen 
<emphasis box="[998,1010,1886,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">e</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis box="[1050,1058,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">f</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[1097,1290,1885,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, but its label does not indicate which of these it is (Luca Ghiraldi, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">3 The ornithological collection of the Zoological Museum of the Turin University (MZUT) has since the 1990s been hosted at the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (MRSN) in Turin, but the specimens in this collection have retained their</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" box="[199,695,2019,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
MZUT inventory numbers (
<bibRefCitation author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[481,684,2019,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis box="[572,623,2019,2043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
